# Route-level error handling

Use an explicit `try` / `catch` in every async route handler. In `catch`, call `next(error)` so the centralized error middleware can format the response.

Do not rely on unhandled promise rejections from the async handler alone; keep the pattern consistent and obvious at the call site.

```typescript
router.get('/path', requireUser, async (req, res, next) => {
  try {
    const result = await SomeService.doThing(req.user.id);
    res.json({ data: result });
  } catch (error) {
    next(error);
  }
});
```

Sync handlers that can throw should use the same shape if they delegate to code that throws.
